<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id521f3116-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s4"><num value="4">§ 4.</num><heading> Precedence of associate justices</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Associate justices shall have precedence according to the seniority of their commissions. Justices whose commissions bear the same date shall have precedence according to seniority in age.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id521f3117-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646">June 25, 1948, ch. 646</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/869">62 Stat. 869</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id521f3118-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id521f3119-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 322 (<ref href="/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s216">Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 216</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/36/1152">36 Stat. 1152</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Minor changes in phraseology were made.</p>
</note>
</notes>
